cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> first-day declarati=
on</a> in the bankruptcy case, which describes what the company has been up=
 to over the last few months. The points that I would highlight are:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In December 2022, =E2=80=9CBed Bath &a=
mp; Beyond triggered multiple events of defaults under its financing facili=
ties=E2=80=9D and began its slow move=C2=A0into bankruptcy.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Also in December 2022, its financial advisers at =
Lazard =E2=80=9Ccommenced a process to solicit interest in a going-concern =
sale transaction that could be effectuated in chapter 11,=E2=80=9D that is,=
 to find someone who was interested in buying the company out of bankruptcy=
 and continuing to operate its business.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">They failed: By mid-January, =E2=80=9CLazard had engaged with approx=
imately 60 potential investors to solicit interest in serving as a plan spo=
nsor, acquiring some or all of the Debtors=E2=80=99 assets or businesses, o=
r providing postpetition financing,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0but =E2=80=9Cto date, the=
 Company has been yet to identify an executable transaction.=E2=80=9D</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So, as of mid-January, it seems that t=
he company=E2=80=99s plan was to file for bankruptcy, close all its stores,=
 liquidate its inventory and hand whatever cash was left to its creditors.<=
/li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But Bed Bath did have one thing go=
ing for it. It was =E2=80=9Cpart of the =E2=80=98meme-stock=E2=80=99 moveme=
nt started and fueled on Reddit boards and social media websites,=E2=80=9D =
because it =E2=80=9Cchecked the two boxes needed to become a meme-stock: (i=
) a troubled financial situation and (ii) nostalgia value.=E2=80=9D<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So someone had the bright idea of=
 delaying things for a bit by selling tons and tons of stock to Bed Bath=E2=
=80=99s retail shareholders at whatever=C2=A0prices they=E2=80=99d pay. =E2=
=80=9CCertain third-party investors expressed interest in providing the Deb=
tors with substantial equity financing in light of the Company=E2=80=99s de=
pressed share price and continued trading volatility. More specifically, th=
e Debtors were approached by Hudson Bay Capital Management, LP=E2=80=9D abo=
ut a weird stock deal that we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/31266131.261440/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDcvYmVkLWJhdGgtYmV5b25kLXNvbGQtc29tZS1zdG9jaz9jbXBpZD=
1CQkQwNDI0MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xld=
